Crop: The name of the crop cultivated. Crop_Year: The year in which the crop was grown. Season: The specific cropping season State: The Indian state where the crop was cultivated. Area: The total land area (in hectares) under cultivation for the specific crop. Production: The quantity of crop production (in metric tons). Annual_Rainfall: The annual rainfall received in the crop-growing region (in mm). Fertilizer: The total amount of fertilizer used for the crop (in kilograms). Pesticide: The total amount of pesticide used for the crop (in kilograms). Yield: The calculated crop yield (production per unit area).

Five seasons plus whole year

Info from the internet Kharif - crops are sown early-May – usually at the beginning of the first monsoon rain Rabi - crops are sown around mid-November – preferably after the monsoon rains

South-west monsoon lasting from June to September. The season is dominated by the humid southwest summer monsoon, which slowly sweeps across the country beginning in late May or early June. Monsoon rains begin to recede from North India at the beginning of October.
